title: Media fails to cover new Trump shooter details
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi discusses the Media Research Centre Report, which says there were zero articles by big tech on the new Thomas Crooks revelations.  “Why are so many media outlets reluctant to cover this extraordinary development?” Ms Panahi said.  “I just can’t understand this.”

title: Douglas Murray blasts leftist gender ideology as ‘mass miseducation’
description: Author Douglas Murray says the left’s gender ideology naming conventions are fading, claiming it is the product of “mass miseducation”.   “My impression is the days where you have to say Rita (she/her) … I think neither of us ever fell into that era … and I’m very proud that we didn’t,” Mr Murray told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “It’s not just a mass derangement; it’s the product of mass miseducation.”

title: ‘Politics is downstream from culture’: Douglas Murray on Peter Whittle’s mark on public life
description: Author Douglas Murray reflects on the public life of Peter Whittle and how his work involved understanding the close relationship between culture and politics.  “I’d known Peter for a couple of decades … he was a terrific force in British national life,” Mr Murray told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “It was his insight a long time ago … that it is the case that politics is downstream from culture.”

title: American people ‘not buying’ Democrats sympathy for drug dealers
description: BlazeTV host Sara Gonzales calls out the Democrats for sympathising with narco-terrorists and drug dealers.  “I don’t want these people bringing drugs into my country,” Ms Gonzales told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “I believe that my thought process represents the absolute majority of the American people.  “We’re just not buying it anymore.”

title: ‘Cowards’: Albanese government has ‘no backbone’
description: The Australian’s Foreign Editor Greg Sheridan says the Albanese government are “cowards” on the international stage.  Mr Sheridan told Sky News host Peta Credlin that Labor “do nothing”.  “They stand for nothing, they’ve got no backbone.”

title: ‘Party of criminals’: Democrats side with narco-boats and criminals
description: BlazeTV host Sara Gonzales claims Democrats “choose America last” when they’re rhetoric sides with drug cartels and narco-boats.  “Democrats time and time again, they are given the opportunity to choose law and order,” Ms Gonzales told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “They choose these narco-terrorists, they choose the drug dealers, they choose the illegal immigrants and the rapists and the gang members.”

title: 'Healthier than a horse’: New York Times slammed for ‘laughable article’ questioning Trump’s health
description: BlazeTV host Sara Gonzales calls out the New York Times “laughable article” on Trump’s health.  “Not only is his body in perfect health, but his mind is there,” Ms Gonzales told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “He’s healthier than a horse.  “They will try, at whatever the cost, to discredit him.”

title: ‘Stinks to high heaven’: Paul Murray analyses how public servants spend taxpayers’ money
description: Sky News host Paul Murray sheds light on how public servants are spending taxpayers' money.   “Talk about a deal that stinks to high heaven,” Mr Murray said.  “The entitlement that politicians get is also extended to many of the high upper ranking members of the public service.”

title: Queensland University academic under fire for shocking advice on helping victims of bullying
description: Sky News James Macpherson scrutinises a Queensland University academic’s rhetoric on standing up for victims of bullying.  “We start the show tonight with yet another reason … to keep your children well clear of so-called experts,” Mr Macpherson said.  “A Queensland University academic has warned that encouraging children to stand up for victims of bullying is a bad thing … intervening to help … risks disempowering the victim.”

title: ‘I cannot make sense of it’: Number of education bureaucrats has ‘gone through the roof’
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says the number of education bureaucrats has “gone through the roof”.  “The explosion in staffing in schools … I mean the staffing across the education sector excluding teachers has gone through the roof,” Mr Bond said.  “It would seem there is a problem.”

title: ‘Gentle parenting’ facilitating bad school attendance rates
description: Former NSW Police Minister David Elliot says “gentle parenting,” which sees a reduced school attendance, is a "big concern".

title: Government spending growing at ‘faster rate’ than the economy
description: Shadow Treasurer Ted O’Brien says government spending is growing at a “faster rate” than the economy.

title: ‘No ability to grow the economy’: Inflation remains at unsustainable highs
description: EQ Economics Managing Director Warren Hogan discusses inflation, which remains at unsustainable highs.  Mr Hogan told Sky News host Paul Murray that while the private sector is coming back, there is “no ability to grow the economy without creating inflation.”  “We didn’t slow the economy; we didn’t raise the rates high enough in the first place.”

title: ‘Dinner time antisemitism’: Report shows rise in anti-Jewish attacks
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean says that ‘dark actors’ have permitted people to be antisemitic.  Mr Dean told Sky News host Andrew Bolt “all too frequently” we are witnessing “dinner time antisemitism”.  “The mask slips and you get this vile antisemitism in a way that they would never speak about people of whatever ethnicity.”

title: Media Meltdowns: Woke Democrat refuses to answer basic questions before losing election
description: Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power has reacted to far-left Democrat Aftyn Behn’s media disaster before she lost an election.
